name: Souza Lobo - Since 1932

reviews.review_text:
The Best shack in Calangute Beach by far!

Cool English  music and polite staff and a great view.

Unlike other places where only Hindi nonsense is played.

Food was delicious especially  the Golden fried calamari !
10/10

Souza Lobo is located on Calangute Beach and it is best to walk from the main road or hotel to this place.

There are many seating options available, within the main restaurant building or outdoors towards the beach. There are many various size tables to suit singles, couples and large groups.

As with many restaurants in Goa, there are 2 menus - a food menu and a drinks menu. Both of which have a large selection of offerings. The staff will also show you some local catch of the day seafood.

Both drink and food options are of good quality and the restaurant is on the mid level pricing. The Goan fish curry with kingfish is of good flavour. I did ask for the full local spice level. Complementing this curry was fluffy rice and a butter chapatti that was soft and wonderful. The cucumber raita is refreshing and cleanses the palate when combined with the Goan fish curry.

The babimca dessert tasted amazing though the presentation was a little lacking and didn't match the presentation that was on the menu. It was a little sloppy in presentation.

Drinks were good with the papaya shake being of medium consistently and with a good amount of papaya flavour.
Cocktails were good also.

On this occasion the service was generally good though a little slow.

Without being discouraged, we made our way to Calangute Beach for lunch. Our choice was Souza Lobo, a restaurant steeped in history since 1932. The appeal of this establishment not only in its delectable cuisine but also in its picturesque seaside setting. While savouring our meal, we were captivated by the breathtaking sight of the azure sky blending with the ocean. As regular patrons of Souza Lobo since 2016, we can attest to its consistently excellent food and ambience. Despite the relatively high prices, it is a worthwhile indulgence, particularly for an early lunch or brunch during your time in North Goa.

description:
**Discovering Souza Lobo: A Goan Legacy by the Beach**

Nestled in the vibrant heart of Calangute Beach since 1932, Souza Lobo offers a captivating dining experience that blends history, exquisite Goan flavors, and stunning seaside vistas. With an impressive rating of 4.2 stars accumulated from over 10,200 reviews, this restaurant has established itself as a commendable destination for both locals and tourists. The keywords that resonate throughout the reviews include "Goan food," "shacks," "xacuti," and "kingfish," underscoring its commitment to authentic coastal cuisine.

**Ambiance & Design**

Upon arrival at Souza Lobo, guests are welcomed into a beautifully designed restaurant that captures the essence of Goan culture. The establishment features a mix of indoor seating, adorned with rustic wooden furniture, and a charming alfresco dining area that invites diners to soak in the gentle sea breeze and picturesque views of the azure ocean. The vibrant colors and traditional decor are accentuated by soft English music that enhances the relaxed and inviting atmosphere. Photos shared by patrons reveal sunlit tables set against a backdrop of the sea, making it a quintessential spot for both lunch and leisurely dinner.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

Souza Lobo's culinary offerings are diverse, featuring two separate menus for food and drinks, designed to cater to a wide range of palates. Signature dishes that have captured the hearts of diners include the Goan fish curry made with succulent kingfish—a dish celebrated for its rich flavors when prepared with local spices. Accompanying this standout curry, fluffy rice and a wonderfully soft butter chapatti create a delightful meal. Reviewers also rave about the golden fried calamari, praised for its crispiness, while the babimca dessert, despite its less-than-perfect presentation, is reported to deliver a heavenly taste experience. With a good selection of cocktails and freshly prepared fruit shakes, patrons are sure to find something refreshing to complement their meal.

**Customer Experience & Service**

Feedback regarding service at Souza Lobo is generally positive, with staff described as polite and accommodating. While some reviewers have noted that the service can be a tad slow during busy times, the friendliness of the staff and their willingness to offer recommendations—such as showcasing the catch of the day—adds to the overall enjoyable experience. The restaurant caters well to groups of all sizes, ensuring everyone has a comfortable dining experience.

**Popularity & Reviews**

The buzz surrounding Souza Lobo is palpable, evidenced by a strong social media presence and a loyal customer base, many of whom have been returning for years. Reviewers consistently emphasize the restaurant's excellent food quality and the unique dining experience offered by its beachfront location. The price point is considered mid-range, making it accessible for diners seeking either a casual meal or a special occasion. 

**Utilizing Visual Content**

The customer-shared images highlight the inviting ambiance at Souza Lobo, showcasing tables with vibrant dishes set against a breathtaking sea view. The contrast between the colorful presentations of food and the serene ocean backdrop exemplifies why this restaurant is a favorite among visitors. Notable images include diners enjoying meals as they bask in the blissful seaside atmosphere, reinforcing the restaurant's position as a must-visit spot in Goa.

In conclusion, Souza Lobo stands out as a Goan culinary gem with its historical legacy, diverse menu, and delightful setting. Whether indulging in its signature dishes or simply soaking in the surroundings, every visit promises to be a memorable experience.
